From 027ae2bdf81d60934fb832e9f563e70f6caef179 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GloriousEggroll <gloriouseggroll@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 16:00:33 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] audio: smooth decoded media playback
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Update Pulse, MMDevAPI, XAudio2, and Microsoft audio decoder behavior used by the replacement media pipeline.

This covers the audio regressions chased during the session:

- Sky: Children of the Light's in-game theater stream no longer drops into mostly-silent bursts.

- Grandia HD's movie audio can play without the crackling/stutter that was traced to output/logging pressure.

- Underdog Detective [神都不良探] gets decoded video audio without needing stale winetricks overrides.

- The Medium keeps the corrected AAC channel-layout path for C001_51.mp4 without adding a SteamGameId hack.

- Warhammer 40,000: Dakka Squadron keeps audio/video media type negotiation working without the old fake-AAC game branch.

- Kirikiri-engine titles from the removed SteamGameId list use general WMA/AAC decoder behavior instead of forcing the input subtype/tag to PCM.

The Pulse changes keep timer and buffer accounting stable when video playback is producing decoded audio in small bursts.

This version intentionally does not reintroduce DualSense mono/haptic reconnect paths; those endpoints are now treated as removed on unplug and newly created on plug-in.
